text: Kushkaran () is a rural locality (a village) in Kyzyl-Yarsky Selsoviet, Yermekeyevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 74 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 18 km from Yermekeyevo, 6 km from Suyemetovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Yermekeyevsky District
title: Kushkaran
